 :tx/rationale "FUNDAMENTAL INSIGHT: The duplicate detection problem is NOT a tooling problem — it is an ATTENTION ALLOCATION problem. The system has braid task search, spec_graph_neighbors, knowledge_relevance_scan. All work. I used none of them before creating OAO, TSV-3, or the initial CTP tasks. Three duplications in one session despite having the tools to prevent all three. The pattern: when I am in GENERATIVE MODE (producing new ideas), I do not switch to VERIFICATION MODE (checking what exists). These are different cognitive states. Generative mode is divergent — explore the space, follow the reasoning, produce the insight. Verification mode is convergent — query the store, compare with existing, identify overlaps. Asking an agent in generative mode to voluntarily switch to verification mode is a PROCESS OBLIGATION that decays under pressure (SEED.md S2). This is identical to the Basin A/Basin B problem: methodology (verification) competes with creation (generation) for the same attention budget. The solution MUST be structural, not procedural. The agent cannot be TOLD to search first — it must be FORCED to search first by the system architecture."
